Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Senior Software Engineer* position with *American Airlines*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack engineering, cloud-native architecture, and automated systems, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect *the technical depth and operational excellence this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an integrated system using LangChain and LangGraph to translate natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API design, input validation, and reliable execution across distributed services. To ensure high-quality delivery, I engineered a robust observability layer for tracing and structured logging, enabling deep *root cause analysis* and improving system *reliability*. My work focused on optimizing for *low-latency* and *scalability*, directly aligning with American Airlines' commitment to delivering unrivaled digital products. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled scalable file operations across AWS and Google Cloud. I also engineered an Identity & Access Management platform supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, where I implemented *secure practices* and *compliance* measures — both of which required *the kind of systems-level thinking and focus on technical debt management central to this role*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities* and drive impact within an agile environment.

My academic research and mentorship experience have provided a rigorous foundation in technical communication and knowledge-sharing — skills that translate directly into *the collaborative culture and people-first values American Airlines holds*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full lifecycle of high-performance training runs on an HPC cluster, optimizing for scaling and training challenges. Beyond building systems, I led workshops for 50+ students, breaking down complex technical concepts Clearly and accessibly. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to foster individual development — directly mirroring *the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *the American Airlines family and its mission*.

I have always been passionate about *People First* and *Excellence in All We Do* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *American Airlines' mission to Care for People on Life's Journey*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

